  <span id="freeText10108664041880268212" style="display:none">I really liked the overall concept of this book. If we had the ability to change the past, would we and how do we know that we wouldn't bring on a future worse than what we are trying to avoid? <br /><br />The detail of the history of Christopher Columbus was also interesting. I'm not sure where the line of fiction and non is crossed (Card does cite his sources at the end so clearly he did his research!), but the story was certainly engaging.</span>
