    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_108760636" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/108760636" />
    <a title="Lady Knight" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3925432-lady-knight"><img alt="Lady Knight" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1286660845p2/3925432.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/108760636?book_show_action=true">Jun 25, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lady Knight" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lady Knight" href="/user/show/3925432-lady-knight">Lady Knight</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3925432-lady-knight?shelf=science-fiction">science-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3925432-lady-knight?shelf=time-travel">time-travel</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3925432-lady-knight?shelf=adult">adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3925432-lady-knight?shelf=americas">americas</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3925432-lady-knight?shelf=space">space</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3925432-lady-knight?shelf=2009-tbr-pile-read">2009-tbr-pile-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3925432-lady-knight?shelf=on-my-shelf-book">on-my-shelf-book</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer108760636" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1264403437902742579">Orson Scott Card is one of my favorite authors, and this book really cemented his reputation as a master of Science Fiction, in my opinion.<br/><br/>Pastwatch is an organization in the future that has discovered the technology to be able to watch every second of every day ever lived in the history of the world. Many people who work for Pastwatch have their own projects. While researching slavery, it is discovered that someone has previously sent future things into the past so as to change the outcome of h</span>
  <span id="freeText1264403437902742579" style="display:none">Orson Scott Card is one of my favorite authors, and this book really cemented his reputation as a master of Science Fiction, in my opinion.<br /><br />Pastwatch is an organization in the future that has discovered the technology to be able to watch every second of every day ever lived in the history of the world. Many people who work for Pastwatch have their own projects. While researching slavery, it is discovered that someone has previously sent future things into the past so as to change the outcome of history (that outcome is the world we presently live in). More research proves that not only did they change history, they thought they were doing it for the better. In reality, though nothing really improved. But the earth is once again on a path to destruction so long in the making that it can't be averted. A group of scientists decide to change all that, but to do so they must give up not only their lives but history as they know it from 1492 on.<br /><br />Christopher Columbus is picked as the most influential person in history who could have changed the world enough to advert disaster, The Interveners (the ones who changed history the first time) also picked him as the one who could change history. Three scientists go back, one will live among the natives in South America and lay the groundwork for them not only to accept Christianity, but be imune to European diseases, and be advanced enough to welcome the Spanish without becoming their slaves. Another one will live in Haiti and prepare the same groundwork there. The third is prepared to sabotage Columbus' ships if need be so that he cannot return to Spain before the Americas are significantly advanced and prepared to deal with Europeans. <br /><br />All in all this was a wonderful book. My review nowhere near does this book justice. Just sit down with a coffee or tea or whatever and read this book. It is well worth your time, and any true fan of Orson Scott Card will not be disappointed.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1264403437902742579" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

